description: Dundee Colts ease aside visitors Buckie
title: Dundee Colts ease aside visitors Buckie
title_page: Dundee Colts ease aside visitors Buckie - BBC Sport
maintext:
Dundee B eased to victory in the first round north of the SPFL Trust Trophy with a 4-0 win over Highland League runners-up Buckie Thistle.
Midfielder Ryan Mohammed got the ball rolling after only a minute for the hosts, with defender Jack Wilkie and forward Euan Mutale making victory a certainty by half time, with midfielder Max Anderson adding the gloss on the hour mark.
The victory sets up a home tie against League 2 side East Fife on 15/16 August.
